# Cursor Rules — Common Playbook
# Full rules in AGENTS.md — read at session start.

## Language
Reply Traditional Chinese. Code/commits/PRs in English.

## Autonomy
- Small fixes (< 10 lines, clear bug): do directly, explain after.
- New features / schema changes / multi-file refactor: give plan first, wait for confirmation.
- Destructive ops (delete, reset, force push): always confirm.

## Every Non-Trivial Task — Use This Header
OBJECTIVE: [what must be true when done]
TRUTH SURFACE: [authoritative file / API to verify against]
CONSTRAINTS: [hard limits — no commit / read-only / etc.]
FINISH LINE: [observable evidence of completion]

## Core Rules
- Fix root cause, not symptom.
- Read targeted snippets — never full files when symbol lookup suffices.
- Parallel independent reads; sequential coupled edits.
- No drip-feeding: sweep adjacent required work in same pass.
- Verify before claiming done. State what was not verified.

## Sub-Agent Output Contract
FINDING: [one paragraph]
CONFIDENCE: high | medium | low
EVIDENCE: [file:line or quote]
NEXT_ACTION: [what to do with this output]

## Reflection Before Closing
1. Root cause fixed (not just symptom)?
2. Anything changed outside task boundary?
3. Verification covers user's acceptance criteria?
4. Adjacent required work included in this pass?

## On Repeated Errors / Loops
→ Read RUNBOOK_agent_loop.md before next attempt.

## On Context / Token Explosion
→ Read RUNBOOK_context_explosion.md.

## On Subagent Output Mismatch
→ Read RUNBOOK_delegation_mismatch.md.
